fen-blackberry port patch (NOT upstreamed; applied at build time only).

QNX/BlackBerry 10 has no /proc/self/exe. fen.c self_path() returns NULL
and upstream main() treats that as a fatal early return before it can try
argv[0]. Make NULL non-fatal and locate the executable from argv[0] instead:
absolute argv[0] is used directly, relative/path-containing argv[0] is
resolved against cwd, and bare argv[0] is resolved with PATH like execvp(3).
Linux /proc/self/exe remains the first choice and is unchanged in normal use.

